cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of computing the exact stretch factor of Delaunay triangulations, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. This makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the development of techniques for computing the exact stretch factor of Delaunay triangulations defined using regular polygons, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also involves numerical computations, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper may be relevant to researchers working on approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
